net.imglib2.cache.util

Class IntervalKeyLoaderAsLongKeyLoader<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.imglib2.cache.util.IntervalKeyLoaderAsLongKeyLoader<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - Type of pixel store for Cell.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CacheLoader<Long,Cell<A>>

    public class IntervalKeyLoaderAsLongKeyLoader<A>
extends Object
implements CacheLoader<Long,Cell<A>>
    This CacheLoader maps a Long key into an Interval based on a CellGrid. The creation of an appropriate A is then delegated to a CacheLoader that generates an A from an interval. Implementing a CacheLoader that fills Cells of an AbstractCellImg requires a lot of boilerplate code for mapping the Long index of a Cell into the Interval that is backed by the Cell. The IntervalKeyLoaderAsLongKeyLoader generates this mapping and reduces the amount of boilerplate code for the caller.
    Author:
    Philipp Hanslovsky
